item.title: About
item.description: Brazilian jiu-jitsu (BJJ) is a grappling-based martial art and combat sport which focuses on ground fighting to control and submit your opponent. It is the product of the introduction of Japanese jiu jitsu and judo to Brazil in the early 1900s, where it was transformed into a new style by a core group of Brazilian pioneers - most famously the Gracie family, who can trace their ancestry back to George Gracie of Dumfries wo left for Brazil in 1826.
